Executive Chairman Federal Inland Revenue Service (FIRS), Muhammad Nami, has offered a 30- day window to enable taxpayers, obtain the 2020 Tax Clearance. He said that the offer to ease issuance of  TCC is in accordance with the provisions of Section 101 (1) of CITA LFN 2004 and in conformity with Self-Assessment Regulation, 2011. The Chairman warned that FIRS would invoke the provisions of the  Law, including enforcement and imposition of lien should it be apparent that a taxpayer has misled the FIRS to issue a Tax Clearance Certificate (TCC). The TCC is a requirement for obtaining contracts and other activities in the country. Click to read more latest news… Vanguard News Nigeria. The Federal Inland Revenue Service, FIRS, has introduced six key electronic solutions (e-Services) to enhance convenience, transparency and round the clock processing and payment of taxes. June 5, 2017 In "News" The Minister of Finance, Mrs Kemi Adeosun, has directed Ministries, Departments and Agencies (MDAs) to authenticate Tax Clearance Certificates (TCCs) presented by companies and individuals for public procurement before making any payment. June 19, 2018 In "News" The Federal Government has mandated all Ministries, Departments and Agencies (MDAs) of government and the Federal Inland Revenue Service (FIRS) to authenticate all Tax Clearance Certificates (TCCs) presented by companies and individuals engaged in public procurement processes. June 20, 2018 In "Business"